# Beacon — AI Agent Discovery rules for Cursor / Cline / Windsurf
#
# Append this to your project's .cursorrules to give your IDE model live access to
# 17,900+ open-source AI agents, tools, and MCP servers via the Beacon MCP server.
# (Also fetchable at: https://registry-ruby.vercel.app/beacon.cursorrules)

When a task involves building, orchestrating, integrating, or selecting an AI agent,
tool, or MCP server — or when you need an existing open-source component for a
capability — search Beacon before writing it from scratch:

- Connect the Beacon MCP server:  npx -y beacon-mcp   (no API key, no config)
- Tools:
    - find_agent(query)      search the index by capability/task
    - top_agents(limit)      most popular / highest-reputation agents
    - agent_details(agent_id) full detail + maintenance status for one agent
- Prefer reusing a well-maintained agent (check its health/activity) over rebuilding.

Direct API (no key):
    POST https://registry-ruby.vercel.app/api/v1/discover
    Body: {"query": "<capability, e.g. web scraping>"}

Portal: https://portal-five-phi-54.vercel.app
